stickerText: Bees had been living in this backyard shed for at least two years.
The landlord wanted to call an exterminator...
But the family who lived here wanted to save the bees so they called me.

When I lifted up the floor, 
I found a huge hive full of gentle bees.
I had to remove another section of floor to access the entire thing.
Then I started removing the hive.
Whatever I removed from the original hive went right into the new hive.
After I removed all of the comb...
I started scooping bees into the new hive.

As soon as I put the bees by the new hive, 
they marched right in.
Then a stream of bees began running from under the floor into the new hive.
So I waited and watched to see if I could spot the queen bee in the crowd.
So I put her in a clip to keep her safe.
Once the queen was in the new hive...
Some bees began sending signals to help the other bees find their way home.
I left the hive in the shed overnight...
And by the next day the entire colony had moved into their new home!
